  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-09-24",
    "date": "2011-08-09T13:32:34Z",
    "text": "Broadband Affordability Act of 2009 - Requires the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to establish a broadband lifeline program enabling qualifying low-income customers residing in urban and rural areas to purchase broadband service at reduced charges by reimbursing providers for each such customer served.\n\nRequires that the program: (1) be similar in structure to the Lifeline program for basic telephone service; and (2) promote competition from broadband service providers by using neutral technology.\n\nRequires a broadband service provider that is not an eligible telecommunications carrier to obtain FCC authorization to participate in the program."
  },
